Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Irrigation Automation Market

The irrigation automation market is expected to witness market growth at a rate of 19.4% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028 and is expected to reach USD 2.98 billion by 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on irrigation automation market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecast period while providing their impacts on the marketâ€™s growth. The rise in the acceptance of modern techniques of irrigation is escalating the growth of irrigation automation market.

Automatic irrigation includes the combination of hardware components, such as sensors, controllers, valves, sprinklers and other components, in a way to build an automated system for both agricultural and non-agricultural applications.

Major factors that are expected to boost the growth of the irrigation automation market in the forecast period are the rise in the acceptance of advanced and improvised technology. Furthermore, the growing initiatives taken by the government that support in the promoting water conservation is further anticipated to propel the growth of the irrigation automation market. Moreover, the increase in the knowledge amongst the farmers about the advantages of automated irrigation technologies is further estimated to cushion the growth of the irrigation automation market. On the other hand, managing of data and data aggregation in irrigation automation systems is further projected to impede the growth of the irrigation automation market in the timeline period.

In addition, the occurrence of large area in the form of farms around the world will further provide potential opportunities for the growth of the irrigation automation market in the coming years. However, the growing cost of installation and unobtainability of skilled personal might further challenge the growth of the irrigation automation market in the near future.

